Managed to run podman on Ryzen Hackintosh. If someone would like to achieve the same, only change I made is this:
```diff
diff --git a/pkg/machine/qemu/options_darwin_amd64.go b/pkg/machine/qemu/options_darwin_amd64.go
index ff8d10db1..dbdf06647 100644
--- a/pkg/machine/qemu/options_darwin_amd64.go
+++ b/pkg/machine/qemu/options_darwin_amd64.go
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@ var (
 )

 func (v *MachineVM) addArchOptions() []string {
-       opts := []string{"-machine", "q35,accel=hvf:tcg", "-cpu", "host"}
+       opts := []string{"-machine", "q35,accel=tcg"}
        return opts
 }
 ```
Then all you have to do is follow `build_osx.md` and you should be good to go. Also, note on `-cpu host`: this is supported only in kvm or hvf acceleration so CPU model detection won't be available inside podman machine.
